Author:
Vol / Page: 2/126
Edition: 1961
Quote: Lieut [sic] Pickersgill ... shot a White Hern which answers exactly with Mr Pennants discription of the White Herns that either now are or were formerly in England. [ed. fn] kotuku <i> Egretta alba modesta </i> (Gray) The European form is <i> E. alba alba </i> Linn.
Notes: The </i> hern</i> of Cook is a dialectal variant of heron: cf Tennyson's `The Brook': I come from haunts of coot and hern

